<TEXT>
Tired of reading paperbacks? Panasonic Business Systems, part of Japan's
Matsushita consumer electronics group, has launched a portable palm-top
player for books published electronically on 8cm compact discs.
Similar in size to a paperback novel, the battery- or mains-powered
Panasonic KX-EBP1 player includes a keyboard, LCD screen, audio and video
