<HEADLINE>
FT  06 AUG 92 / UK Company News: Chieftain 20% ahead at Pounds 620,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Profits of Chieftain Group, the USM-quoted supplier of specialist insulation
and fireproofing services, rose from Pounds 517,000 to Pounds 620,000
pre-tax for the six months ended June 30.
The 20 per cent improvement was achieved from a turnover Pounds 1.22m ahead
at Pounds 7.63m. Earnings rose by 0.83p to 4.85p and the interim dividend is
being lifted from 1.9p to 2.1p.
Mr Peter Wardle, the chairman, said the group was well supported from its
activities in selected sectors of industrial construction, shipbuilding and
offshore oil and gas.
He added that his 1991 year-end forecast that 'we would see some improvement
in market conditions in 1992' was late in coming. However, he went on to say
that 'given that there will be some improvement, we anticipate the progress
achieved in the first half of 1992 will be maintained for the full year.'
At the half year-end the order book was standing at Pounds 12m.
</TEXT>
