FT  06 AUG 92 / More Swedes out of work
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   STOCKHOLM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Swedish unemployment soared in July to 307,000 or 6.5 per cent of the
workforce, the highest figure in half a century, writes Robert Taylor in
Stockholm.
Mr Gote Bernhardsson, head of AMS, the labour market board, warned that
Sweden's internationally famous labour market system with its emphasis on
training and work for the unemployed was under threat as a result of the
rapid escalation in the jobless total. The figure has more than doubled in a
year.
