FT  06 AUG 92 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
DESPITE RELATIVELY slow buying interest from Japanese brokers, Australian
wool sale reports indicate a generally firm and unchanged market in the
second week of the new selling season. There was some disappointment when
wool sold at virtually unchanged prices after the July recess, but no
downturn followed. The Australian Wool Corporations market indicator, which
closed at 545c/kg at the end of June, was down to 535c/kg on August 5, but
this was only one cent down on the previous day. In the wool using industry
some sectors are busy but others are more directly affected by recession and
continue to find trade difficult.
