profits were offset by the continuing slump in the hardware distribution
business.
Net earnings fell to CDollars 38.4m (USDollars 32.4m), or 66 cents a share,
in the three months to June 30, the first quarter of the company's fiscal
year. Earnings a year earlier were CDollars 39.3m, or 71 cents a share.
