earlier.
Diversey Corporation, the international cleaning services subsidiary, lifted
profits by 10 per cent, thanks largely to gains in the UK and Germany. But
sales in North America were soft and margins were eroded by stiff
competition.
Beaver Lumber's profit fell by 16 per cent, reflecting the unexpectedly
protracted recession in Canada.
Molson said it expected the business recovery to gain momentum later this
year, but at a 'moderate rate'.
